We can extract the $7^2$, $2^4$ and $3^2$, that makes \begin{align*}&=\sqrt{7^2\cdot 2^4 \cdot3^2}\end{align*}
Now take the roots of the perfect squares outside the root:
\begin{align*}7\cdot 4\cdot 3&=84 \end{align*}
